38. Interpret the steps to iterate over a PHP array using a while loop with an example
<?php
$colors = array("Red", "Green", "Blue");
reset($colors); // move pointer to first element
while (($value = current($colors)) !== false) {
    echo "Color: " . $value . "<br>";
    next($colors); // move pointer forward
}
?>
Output:
Color: Red
Color: Green
Color: Blue
